        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "When replaying a macro, the local Nvim \"unnamed\" register (`\"`) is updated but there's no reason to update the _clipboard_ during macro execution. That was the idea behind c826ebd3de7f73d360a8032127ed9d9db0543d8a.\r\n\r\nThe repro steps here involve `<c-r>*` which breaks the assumption of c826ebd3de7f73d360a8032127ed9d9db0543d8a. \r\n\r\n# Proposal\r\n\r\n- `<c-r>*` (and `<c-r>+`) should return the unnamed register during macro execution (`start_batch_changes`).\r\n- More generally, clipboard state should be cached, and Nvim should only update the system clipboard on specific events: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/11804#issuecomment-1113927971",
            "created_at": "2023-10-12T11:34:46Z",
